<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-05-1123 </DOCNO><TEXT>The world refining industry is now facing strong price fluctuations followingcrude oil price instability and the emergence of netback deals whichprevent refiners from planning any long-term investments or capacitypolicies. The Asia-Pacific oil market is likely to be the most dynamicin the coming years. In that market, the flow of products to be expectedfrom the new OPEC source refineries, as well as, government policies,will play a major role. Since traditional planning seems to have lostits relevance, the article suggests that a flexible approach, based onscenario analysis, may be the only rational way for investment planningover the next decade.</TEXT></DOC>